# 1. HTML Structure (index.html, post1.html, post2.html):
index.html (Homepage):
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Simple Blog</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>My Awesome Blog</h1>
        <nav>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="index.html" class="active">Home</a></li>
                <li><a href="post1.html">First Post</a></li>
                <li><a href="post2.html">Second Post</a></li>
                <li><button id="themeToggle">Toggle Theme</button></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
        <section class="post-preview">
            <h2><a href="post1.html">Exploring the Wilderness</a></h2>
            <p class="meta">Published on May 16, 2025</p>
            <p>A brief glimpse into an amazing adventure in the wild...</p>
            <a href="post1.html" class="read-more">Read More</a>
        </section>

        <section class="post-preview">
            <h2><a href="post2.html">The Joy of Coding</a></h2>
            <p class="meta">Published on May 10, 2025</p>
            <p>Reflections on the rewarding experience of writing code and building things...</p>
            <a href="post2.html" class="read-more">Read More</a>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2025 My Simple Blog</p>
    </footer>

    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>

# post1.html (First Blog Post):
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Exploring the Wilderness - My Simple Blog</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>My Awesome Blog</h1>
        <nav>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="index.html">Home</a></li>
                <li><a href="post1.html" class="active">First Post</a></li>
                <li><a href="post2.html">Second Post</a></li>
                <li><button id="themeToggle">Toggle Theme</button></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>
    </header>

    <main class="post-content">
        <article>
            <h2>Exploring the Wilderness</h2>
            <p class="meta">Published on May 16, 2025</p>
            <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/600/8FBC8F/FFFFFF?Text=Wilderness+Image" alt="Wilderness Scene">
            <p>The crisp morning air filled my lungs as I stepped out of the tent. The sounds of nature surrounded me â€“ birds chirping, a gentle breeze rustling through the leaves, and the distant murmur of a flowing stream. This was it, the start of my solo adventure into the heart of the wilderness.</p>
            <p>I had spent weeks planning this trip, poring over maps, packing essentials, and preparing myself mentally for the solitude and challenges ahead. Now, standing at the trailhead, a mix of excitement and trepidation washed over me.</p>
            <p>The path wound its way through dense forest, sunlight filtering through the canopy in dappled patterns. Each step crunched on fallen leaves and twigs, the only sound besides my own breathing. I marveled at the towering trees, their ancient presence a humbling reminder of the power of nature.</p>
            <p>As the day progressed, I encountered wildlife â€“ a curious deer grazing in a meadow, a hawk circling overhead, and the fleeting glimpse of a fox disappearing into the undergrowth. These moments of connection with the natural world were profound and deeply satisfying.</p>
            <p>By evening, I reached a secluded clearing beside a tranquil lake. Setting up camp as the sun dipped below the horizon, painting the sky in hues of orange and purple, I felt a sense of peace and accomplishment. Sitting by the crackling campfire, under a blanket of stars, I reflected on the day's journey and the incredible beauty of the wilderness.</p>
            <p>This was just the first day, and I knew there were more challenges and wonders to come. But in that moment, surrounded by the serene embrace of nature, I felt truly alive.</p>
        </article>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2025 My Simple Blog</p>
    </footer>

    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>

