/* Responsive Design */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    nav ul {
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: center;
    }

    nav li {
        margin-bottom: 0.5em;
    }

    main {
        margin: 10px;
        padding: 15px;
    }
}

/* Dark Theme */
body.dark-theme {
    background-color: #1e1e1e;
    color: #f5f5f5;
}

body.dark-theme header {
    background-color: #333;
    color: #f5f5f5;
}

body.dark-theme nav a {
    color: #f5f5f5;
}

body.dark-theme nav a:hover {
    background-color: #555;
}

body.dark-theme main {
    background-color: #2c2c2c;
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
}

body.dark-theme .post-preview h2 a {
    color: #f5f5f5;
}

body.dark-theme .meta {
    color: #bbb;
}

body.dark-theme .read-more {
    background-color: #007bff;
    color: #f5f5f5;
}

body.dark-theme .read-more:hover {
    background-color: #0056b3;
}

body.dark-theme footer {
    background-color: #333;
    color: #f5f5f5;
}

/* Theme Toggle Button */
#themeToggle {
    background: none;
    color: #fff;
    border: none;
    padding: 0.5em 1em;
    cursor: pointer;
    border-radius: 5px;
    font-size: 1em;
}

#themeToggle:hover {
    background-color: #555;
}

body.dark-theme #themeToggle {
    color: #f5f5f5;
}

3. JavaScript Interactivity (script.js):
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const themeToggle = document.getElementById('themeToggle');
    const body = document.body;
    const currentTheme = localStorage.getItem('theme') || 'light';

    if (currentTheme === 'dark') {
        body.classList.add('dark-theme');
    }

    themeToggle.addEventListener('click', () => {
        body.classList.toggle('dark-theme');
        const newTheme = body.classList.contains('dark-theme') ? 'dark' : 'light';
        localStorage.setItem('theme', newTheme);
    });
});

Key Points:
 * Semantic HTML: We're using elements like <header>, <nav>, <main>, <article>, <section>, and <footer> to structure the content semantically.
 * Responsive Design: The CSS includes a media query to adjust the layout for smaller screens, making the navigation vertical.
 * JavaScript Interactivity: A simple theme toggle feature is implemented using JavaScript and localStorage to persist the user's preference.
 * Multi-Page Navigation: The <nav> element provides links to different pages of the blog.
